Roles & ResponsibilitiesBusiness context and main purpose of job: Being part of Transformation Office, this role serves as a liaison between business users and vendors, working on projects for Singapore. Key accountabilities:  Facilitate the definition of user requirement with business, conduct performance gap analysis, prepare requirement package (e.g. Business Requirement Specification, Process Map, Product Roadmap, Requirement Traceability Matrix, etc.); Understand and review To-Be processes, suggesting areas of improvements for As-Is processes; Work with stakeholders on scope and requirements management; Review requirements documented by vendors, ensuring all requirements are adequately defined in the Functional Design documents prior to sign-off from stakeholders; Function as a Project Manager when required;
 Lead business users in defining UAT test cases, ensuring all requirements are tested; Facilitate/Conduct user training for all users, off-shore teams and other departments using the application; Ensure all deliverables by the vendor are on-time.  Requirements University graduate preferably in Information Technology, Computer Science or related disciplines; Minimum 7 years of experience in Business requirement gathering & analysis, User Acceptance Test and User Management, with experience in General Insurance an added advantage; Project Management experience is a plus; Strong analytical and problem solving skills are required; Organized, structured and able to do detailed work and documentation; Experienced in Vendor Management; Excellent communication and interpersonal skills; Working experience in using Visio and documenting As-Is/To-Be processes and Use Case model;
 Be able to make occasional travel to other Asian countries when needs arise.

Roles & ResponsibilitiesAn exciting opportunity as a Business Analyst with a global bank in their service delivery team for the overall productivity and optimization initiatives. RequirementsMandatory Skillsets
  Degree in Computer Science / Information Technology / Mathematics / Statistics;
 At least 2 years of Business Analyst experience in finance services or strong in numbers;
 Good understanding in overall IT space i.e. Infrastructure and/or Software Development;
 Strong and positive to take up new domain and challenges;
 Proficient in Excel, reports development and data analysis;
 Analytical, detail-oriented and solution-oriented;
 Resourceful, independent and proactive team player;
 Good communication skills, good grasp of the current state and evolution of financial markets.
  Desired Skillsets
  Banking / Finance Services experience is preferred;  Roles & Responsibilities
  Part of the Service Delivery Team to support analysis of data and service delivery matters to various business units;
 Collect, collate and analyse data and translate to reports, summary, recommendations as well as deriving financial value for internal stakeholders;
 Manage and track day-to-day financial dollar value activities for projects;
 Develop adhoc reports from trends and current consumption;
 Support productivity and service optimization initiatives and projects from start to delivery;
 Coordinate data centre relocation projects working with various technical teams and architects to ensure service delivery is optimized.  Should you be interested in this opportunity, please send your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest. Confidentiality is assured, and only short-listed candidates will be notified.
  EA License: 07C5639

Roles & ResponsibilitiesAn exciting opportunity as a Technical Business Analyst for a top global bank for new initiatives into traditional databases and Big Data Technologies. RequirementsMandatory Skillsets
  Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or Computer Engineering;
 Good business domain and experience in banking systems;
 Good knowledge and experience in SDLC;
 Proficient hands-on experience in Oracle 11g, SQL and Unix Shell Scripting;
 Adept in leveraging latest technologies, best practices and lead in the formation of effective information analytics expertise;
 Excellent command over verbal/ written English and presentation to engage business stakeholders and good leadership skills;
 Organised and positive working attitude, with the ability to work independently and as a team.  Desired Skillsets
  Big Data experience / exposure / knowledge is preferred.  Roles & Responsibilities
  Responsible for providing data management solutions for business users;
 Prepare and plan server and application migration;
 Responsible for batch executions and implementation activities;
 Engage end-users to understand business data and reporting requirements;
 Collaborate with technical teams on the design and delivery of the solution;
 Meet project deadlines, identify project obstacles, proactively mitigate risks and escalate and resolve issues effectively;
 Ensure team alignment on project goals, objectives and business outcomes.  Should you be interested in this opportunity, please send your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest. Confidentiality is assured, and only short-listed candidates will be notified.
   EA License: 07C5639

